## Description

Understand how the Unity API Specification is used in building both Client Engagement Applications and Provider Services.

The Unity API specification is managed using SwaggerHub (an online team collaboration service). The Unity API specification is defined using the commercial OpenAPI 3.0 standard.  The OpenAPI 3.0 standard is supported by numerous tooling for documentation, code generation and API management. ([https://www.openapis.org/](https://www.openapis.org/))

 ![](data:image/*;base64,)

Unity API Spec documentation is presented to stakeholders via a GitHub Pages Website.  The documentation consists of an overview, design/architecture principles, code snippets, and endpoint definitions and executable explorer environment.  The Unity API endpoint definitions are generated directly from the Unity API Spec yaml file using Redoc technology.

The Aspenware Unity Platform and associated Aspenware Unity Appliances implement the Unity API Specification.  Aspenware uses Swashbuckle technology to manage our OpenAPI v3 compliance.
